 Hardware Wallet Method (Highly Recommended)**\nSince you are planning to buy a BitBox02, the absolute easiest and safest way to figure this out is to **wait until the device arrives.**\n1. When you get the BitBox02, choose the option to \"Restore an existing wallet\" (rather than creating a new one).\n2. Enter your 11 known words, and guess \"meadow\" for the 8th word. \n3. The BitBox02 calculates the checksum entirely offline, right on the device. If \"meadow\" is wrong, the device will immediately tell you \"Invalid Checksum.\"\n4. If it fails, simply try again with \"method\", and then \"matrix\". \n5. Once the device accepts the phrase, you have found your exact word. Because the BitBox02 is an isolated, offline environment, your keys never touch an internet-connected device.\n\n**Option B: The Air-Gapped Computer Method (For Advanced Users)**\nIf you are in a rush and cannot wait for the hardware wallet, you can use a trusted open-source tool like the *Ian Coleman BIP39 Converter*. However, to do this securely, you must do it on an \"air-gapped\" machine.\n1. Download the tool\u0027s HTML file to a USB drive.\n2. Boot an old computer into a live, temporary operating system (like Tails OS or Ubuntu on a USB stick) with the WiFi and Ethernet physically disconnected.\n3. Open the HTML file in the offline browser, type in your variations, and see which one produces a valid checksum.\n4. Turn off the computer. Because it was running a live operating system in RAM, all memory of your seed phrase is permanently wiped the second the computer loses power.\n\n**Summary:**\nDo not type your seed phrase into any website, app, or standard computer to test it. Wait for your BitBox02 to arrive, type the variations directly into the physical device, and let the hardware securely do the math for you!",
